    "where c(ϕ) = ∑ r c(r, ϕ) 107.",
    "To perform sparsity correction for each neuron, we generate 100 null-matched neurons in which the spatial bin of each spike is replaced by a random value uniformly distributed across spatial bins.",
    "We subtract the mean I(ϕ) over the null matches from the I(ϕ) for the true data.",
    "To calculate the average difference in information between sparse and dense phases, we first use f(ϕ) to partition ϕ into sparse and dense halves.",
    "We then average the sparsitycorrected I(ϕ) over each half, apply a ReLU function to each half to prevent negative information values, and compute the difference between halves."
